column5: I can remember like yesterday catching 9-10" brown trout in small creeks as a young kid and thought they fought hard. But to hook into this monster really takes the cake...  http://www.jsonline.com/sports/outdoors/98649849.html
wow. Big much? That thing is huge. Looks like it might have been sitting in the sun for a while. lol

Better make sure they get it exactly right. On paper it's only 1/2 an ounce heavier than the brown caught last September in the Manistee river. Seems lake Michigan currently has a strong year class of monster browns, wow!
Awesome, wish we still had some freakish browns in Lake O , I think we need to get ahold of that strain and get them in Lake O. in the "old" days browns in the mid 30"s used to come out of lake O.
There are browns on the better side of Lake NY.....LOL..
Thats huge.    I remember seeing some bigg,ns during the salmon derby years ago aswell.

What a Slab!!!  I remember when the record Brown was 34.88 or something like that . . . caught here right in good old Ontario (from shore by a relatively famous angler).  This fish dwarfs that one . . . a monster.
WOW, that thing is a friggen beast.
2010 year of the giants! I predict a record size muskie some time soon.
Is that one of those genetically altered mutants?
Ill let you all know when i get her!!
Do you me a new PB for ya Will?  LOL!
lake michigan has the best brown trout fishing in the world...milwakee or however you spell it
